  "text": "Quarter-final · 10 July 2026 · Los Angeles. Final score: Spain 2–1 Belgium. Spain broke Belgian hearts with a late winner to reach the semi-finals.\n\nTwo of Europe's most talented squads traded blows in Los Angeles, with a semi-final against France waiting for the winner.\n\nThe goals, in sequence: 30′ Fabián Ruiz — 1–0; 41′ Charles De Ketelaere — 1–1; 88′ Mikel Merino — 2–1. That is 3 goals in all, Spain accounting for 2 and Belgium 1.\n\nFabián Ruiz turned in an early opener, slotting home a rebound to give Spain control. Charles De Ketelaere levelled for Belgium, keeping his own fine tournament going and setting up a tense finale. The decisive moment arrived in the 88th minute: Merino pounced on a shot from Cubarsí that goalkeeper Senne Lammens spilled into his path, and Spain were through. Spain's blend of youth and control looked increasingly like that of a side built to go all the way.\n\nMomentum, as ever in the knockouts, proved a fragile and fleeting thing.\n\nThe expected-goals picture tightened around every set piece and transition.\n\nFine margins decided it, as they so often do at this stage of a tournament.\n\nFor the record, Spain advanced. Goal, team and minute for every event above are Merkle-proven on Solana devnet via TxLINE; the scorer names are attributed from public match reports and aligned to the verified goals by team and order. Nothing here rests on the commentator's word alone.",
